Prompt:
“I am preparing for a Java interview. I will provide you with one topic. For that topic, give me a complete interview preparation set including:

Theory questions

Practical coding questions

Tricky & logical questions

Advanced / complex questions

Real-world scenario questions

Debugging questions

Optimization questions

Architecture & design questions

Behavioral + technical questions

MCQs / quick quiz

Hands-on coding tasks

System design questions (Java-specific)

Testing (JUnit / Mockito) questions

Best practices & anti-patterns
Minimum 100 questions (you may give more).
Make the list structured and categorized.
Do not include answers unless I ask for them.
Wait for my topic.”

